984:12', '## Key Facts & Timeline
- Case: Erika C. Turner v. Chong Suk Thwaites, Circuit Court of Mobile County, AL, No. 02‑CV‑2024‑900285. Video deposition of Michael G. Koslin, D.M.D., taken December 22, 2025 at 1:27 PM. Wreck alleged to have occurred October 12, 2022 (the deposition concerns possible relation of medical conditions to that wreck).  
- Dr. Koslin testified he treated Ms. Turner (specific treatment details not included in the pages provided).  
- Dr. Koslin retired about five weeks before the deposition (i.e., late November/early December 2025) but remains licensed and maintains board certification.

## People Mentioned (with roles)
- Erika C. Turner — Plaintiff / patient (case subject).  
- Chong Suk Thwaites — Defendant.  
- Michael G. Koslin, D.M.D. — Deponent; oral & maxillofacial surgeon; treating provider for Ms. Turner; admitted as plaintiff’s expert in OMFS.  
- Alexander Kirkland — Plaintiff’s counsel (introduced at start).  
- Harrison Shelton — Defense counsel (introduced at start).  
- Nicole Mays, CCR — Court reporter / commissioner.  
- Rod Pruett — Videographer.  
- Mobile Bay Reporting / Birmingham Reporting Service — reporting firms referenced.  
- Exhibits referenced (need review): Plaintiff’s Exhibit 1 — Medical Record (page 59 of index); Defendant’s Exhibit 1 — Medical Record (page 41).

## Injuries & Medical Findings
- The pages provided do not include any substantive description of Ms. Turner’s injuries, objective findings, imaging, diagnoses, treatment rendered, or prognosis.  
- What is established in this portion:
  - Dr. Koslin is the treating oral/maxillofacial surgeon for Ms. Turner (implies dental/facial/oral injuries may be at issue).  
  - He is qualified and agreed to give medical opinions relevant to causation (he was formally stipulated as an expert by counsel).

## Liability & Damages Details (fault indicators, comparative negligence, medical causation, treatment gaps)
- Fault / comparative negligence: No discussion in the provided pages about the mechanics of the wreck, fault allocation, or comparative negligence.  
- Medical causation: Dr. Koslin acknowledged the case is about relating medical conditions to the October 12, 2022 wreck and agreed to render expert opinions; however, no explicit causation opinions appear in the excerpt.  
- Treatment gaps / records: Exhibits include medical records (Plaintiff’s Ex. 1 and Defendant’s Ex. 1), but the excerpt does not summarize them. No information provided here about timing between accident and first treatment, continuity of care, gaps in treatment, prior conditions, or recommended future care/costs.  
- Availability/credibility issues to note: recent retirement (five weeks earlier) — he still maintains licensure and board certification. Confirm whether retirement affects availability for trial (likely not but should be verified) and whether his records remain accessible.

## Bottom Line
- Positive for plaintiff: Dr. Michael Koslin is a highly credentialed oral and maxillofacial surgeon (43 years’ practice, American Board certified, ongoing CME) who treated Erika Turner and has been formally stipulated as the plaintiff’s expert. That foundation is necessary in Alabama to tie facial/dental/oral injuries to the October 12, 2022 wreck and is established in this portion of the deposition.  
- Missing / next steps (critical): The excerpt provided stops short of substantive medical opinions and treatment history. To evaluate strength of plaintiff’s medical causation and damages proof, obtain and review:
  - The remainder of Dr. Koslin’s deposition (pages after 15) for specific diagnoses, exam findings, imaging, causation opinions (percentage/“more likely than not”), chronology of care, surgeries/procedures performed or recommended, permanency opinions, and cost/lost‑wage estimates.  
  - Plaintiff’s Ex. 1 and Defendant’s Ex. 1 (medical records referenced) to confirm dates, objective findings, pre‑existing conditions, referrals, imaging, and billing.  
  - Confirm Dr. Koslin’s availability for trial despite recent retirement and whether he will be able to provide live testimony and affidavits if needed.  
- Flags that could help plaintiff’s case:
  - Dr. Koslin’s long experience and board certification — strong credibility as a treating expert.  
  - He accepted the expert designation on the record (stipulation by defense counsel) — removes fight over qualification and streamlines admissibility of his opinions.  
- Recommended follow‑up topics for deposition/questions if not covered later: prior TMJ/dental/jaw conditions, first date of treatment post‑accident, temporal relationship of symptoms to accident, objective imaging results, treatment plan and prognosis, need for future procedures, apportionment to pre‑existing vs accident, and foundation for any causation opinions (mechanism linking the crash to specific injuries).', 'Deposition Transcript', 1, 'Admin', 256448, '2026-03-12T21:03:29.319Z', 'firm', 5, 0, NULL, NULL, '{}', NULL, 'complete', NULL),
