Narrative
Turner, Erika / Run 216007
2022-10-12
Printed by Cranford, Shannon R [322]

On 2022-10-12 122, call-sign 122, with Fountain, Carolyn O. [EMR] and Smith, Victoria [ALS] aboard was
dispatched at 14:00:49 to HILLVIEW RD / AIRPORT BLVD in Mobile for a traffic / transportation incident
complaint. 122 rolled at 14:01:13, drove emergent at normal traffic speed, and arrived at 14:19:26.

The patient was found at 14:20:26 in emergent (yellow) condition. The patient is a 57-year-old adult female,
alert and fully oriented, breathing normally on room air. Vitals were taken at 14:23:55 (Patient contact +
00:03:29), and all findings were within normal ranges. EMS decided the patient required transport for
dizziness mvc not available at origin. Patient required stretcher transportation due to monitoring
requirement - danger to self or others (Mvc). Patient was moved to the stretcher by unassisted ambulation,
then to the ambulance and made secure.

Transport commenced at 14:26:08, proceeding emergent at normal traffic speed, and lasted for 2 minutes.
The patient was in a semi-fowlers position throughout the transport. Patient was alert and fully oriented. An
assessment was performed at 14:26:08 (Transporting + 00:00:00) upon the patient''s complaint of
"Dizziness" which began 1 hours ago, although all exam findings were normal. Vitals were taken one
minute later: since vitals were recorded earlier, mild tachycardia (HR 101) developed.

The patient exam found one acute symptom: Neurological: Weakness (R53.1).

122 ended transport at USA HEALTH FREESTANDING ED at 14:28:53. EMS moved the patient by
stretcher into the hospital. At that time the patient was still in emergent (yellow) condition. EMS transferred
responsibility for the patient at 14:33:35.
Patient was waiting at the red light when she was hit from behind. Restrained, no LOC, hit mouth on
steering wheel. Patient stated that she was slightly dizzy but overall felt fine. She wanted an evaluation at
the closest facility.

