the inspection and copying commanded.
(2) (A) A person commanded to produce and permit inspection and copying of designated books, papers, document or tangible things, or inspection of premises
need not appear in person at the place of production or inspection unless commanded to appear for deposition, hearing or trial.
(c) Protection of person subject to subpoenas.
(1) A party or an attorney responsible for the issuance and service of a subpoena shall take reasonable steps to avoid imposing undue burden or expense on a
person subject to that subpoena. The court from which the subpoena was issued shall enforce this duty and impose upon the party or attorney in breach of this
duty on appropriate sanction, which may include, but is not limited to, lost earnings and a reasonable attorney fee.
