2 
 
 
 3. This  request  shall  be  considered  ongoing  in  nature  and  shall  require  the 
production  of  records  from  any, and  all  future  care  and  treatment  of  the 
above-named patient. 
 
           4. All parties to this action have received notice of this party’s intent to have 
this subpoena issued, and THIS IS A COURT ORDER. 
 
 Production and inspection are to take place at the place where the documents or things are 
regularly kept or at some other reasonable place designated by you.   
 You  have  the  option  to  deliver  or  mail  legible  copies  of  documents  or  things  to  the 
requesting  attorney, MATTHEW  A.  LAYMON,  ESQUIRE,  Webster,  Henry,  Bradwell, 
Cohan,  Speagle  &  DeShazo,  P.C., 29000  US  Highway  98,  Building  C,  Suite 202, Daphne, 
Alabama, 36526, but you may condition such activity on your part upon the payment in advance 
by the party causing the issuance of this subpoena of the reasonable costs of the making of such 
copies.    If  you  require  prepayment,  please email your  invoice  to  the  attention of Annie  Finch, 
Paralegal, at afinch@websterhenry.com.  If  you  do  not  require  prepayment,  please  send  an 
invoice for the cost of copying the records.  Please indicate your Federal Tax ID number on your 
statement.    An  invoice  itemizing  the  copying  charges  and  number  of  pages  copied  must  be 
submitted.   Please note that if you decide to copy and mail the requested documents and/or tangible 
things, Defendant only agrees to pay all reasonable costs incurred by you in copying the requested 
records.   Reasonable costs, as defined in Code of Alabama, § 12-21-6.1, are: not more than one 
dollar ($1.00) for each page of the first 25 pages, not more than 50 cents ($.50) for each page in 
excess of 25 pages, a search fee of five dollars ($5.00) and actual costs for mailing the records.  
Should the cost of making such copies be more than $200.00, please call before proceeding with 
production. 
