  (41, 14, 1, 'Newman''s Medical Services, Inc. (Ambulance). EMS providers: Smith, Victoria [ALS - Paramedic], Fountain, Carolyn O. [EMR / First Responder]. Destination: USA Health Freestanding ED / USA Medical Center', '2022-10-12T00:00:00.000Z', 'EMS transport for complaint of dizziness (onset ~1 hour) after MVC (rear-ended; hit mouth on steering wheel). Procedures/treatments performed: stretcher transport (semi‑fowlers position), vital signs (automated cuff, pulse oximetry) x2, general physical assessment. Patient-reported pain level: Pain 0/10; reported feeling slightly dizzy. Progress/functional status: alert and fully oriented, moved to stretcher by unassisted ambulation, condition documented as Emergent (Yellow); overall status documented as Unchanged. Diagnoses/ICD codes: Dizziness / Giddiness R42 (primary impression); Neurological weakness R53.1 (acute symptom). Objective findings: Vitals at 14:23:55 — BP 125/95, MAP 105, HR 100, SpO2 99%, RR 16, Temp 98.0°F, GCS 15; at 14:27:04 — BP 126/96, MAP 106, HR 101 (mild tachycardia), SpO2 98%, RR 16, Temp 97.0°F. Orthostatic assessed (Yes). Neuro/mental exam normal for baseline; oriented x4; pupils 3 mm; capillary refill <2 seconds. Lungs, heart, head, neck, spine, abdomen, extremities documented normal on exam. No LOC reported. Referrals/recommendations/plan: transported to USA Health Freestanding ED / USA Medical Center for further evaluation and transferred care (transfer of care signed).', '2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10', 'EMS transport for complaint of dizziness (onset ~1 hour) after MVC (rear-ended; hit mouth on steering wheel). Procedures/treatments performed: stretcher transport (semi‑fowlers position), vital signs (automated cuff, pulse oximetry) x2, general physical assessment. Patient-reported pain level: Pain 0/10; reported feeling slightly dizzy. Progress/functional status: alert and fully oriented, moved to stretcher by unassisted ambulation, condition documented as Emergent (Yellow); overall status documented as Unchanged. Diagnoses/ICD codes: Dizziness / Giddiness R42 (primary impression); Neurological weakness R53.1 (acute symptom). Objective findings: Vitals at 14:23:55 — BP 125/95, MAP 105, HR 100, SpO2 99%, RR 16, Temp 98.0°F, GCS 15; at 14:27:04 — BP 126/96, MAP 106, HR 101 (mild tachycardia), SpO2 98%, RR 16, Temp 97.0°F. Orthostatic assessed (Yes). Neuro/mental exam normal for baseline; oriented x4; pupils 3 mm; capillary refill <2 seconds. Lungs, heart, head, neck, spine, abdomen, extremities documented normal on exam. No LOC reported. Referrals/recommendations/plan: transported to USA Health Freestanding ED / USA Medical Center for further evaluation and transferred care (transfer of care signed).', NULL, 0, 'Newman''s Medical Services.pdf', 'application/pdf', NULL, '2026-03-13T12:43:13.213Z', NULL, 58, 'Head/Neck');
